Package sample.uml

Class UMLClass

  • java.lang.Object
    • sample.uml.Element
      • sample.uml.UMLClassifier
        • sample.uml.UMLClass
  • public class UMLClass
extends UMLClassifier
    The class (its instance) represents a class model from UML. Extends the UMLClassifier class. Contains a list of attributes and operations (methods). The class can be abstract.

      • addAttribute

        public boolean addAttribute​(UMLAttribute attr)
        Inserts an attribute into the UML class model. The attribute is inserted at the end of the list (last item). If the class already contains an attribute of the same name, it does nothing.
        Parameters:
        attr - - Inserted attribute.
        Returns:
        Action successful (returns if successful, otherwise false).

      • getAttrPosition

        public int getAttrPosition​(UMLAttribute attr)
        Returns the position of the attribute in the attribute list. The position is indexed from 0. If the class does not contain the attribute, it returns -1.
        Parameters:
        attr - - Searched attribute.
        Returns:
        Attribute position.

      • getAttributeByName

        public UMLAttribute getAttributeByName​(java.lang.String name)
        Returns the position of the attribute with a specific name in the attribute list. The position is indexed from 0. If the class does not contain the attribute, it returns -1.
        Parameters:
        name - - the name of the attribute
        Returns:
        Attribute position.

      • moveAttrAtPosition

        public int moveAttrAtPosition​(UMLAttribute attr,
                              int pos)
        Moves the position of the attribute to the newly specified one. The position is indexed from the value 0. If the class does not contain the given attribute, it does nothing and returns -1. When you move to the pos position, all existing items (attributes) move one position to the right from the pos position (inclusive).
        Parameters:
        attr - - Moved attribute.
        pos - - new position
        Returns:
        Operation success.

      • getAttributes

        public javafx.collections.ObservableList getAttributes()
        Returns an unmodifiable list of attributes. Can be used to display class attributes.
        Returns:
        Non-modifiable attribute list.
